{"add":{"doc":{"id":"a8160ca81d4612aed80e2de0e669eeef165fe253cbeeb0b0a3eeb5a6d2030b63","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/77/Bcrablinter.jpg/220px-Bcrablinter.jpg","previous":["Analysis of banded chromosomes is done at a microscope by a clinical laboratory specialist in cytogenetics (CLSp(CG)). Generally 20 cells are analyzed which is enough to rule out mosaicism to an acceptable level. The results are summarized and given to a board-certified cytogeneticist for review, and to write an interpretation taking into account the patients previous history and other clinical findings. The results are then given out reported in an International System for Human Cytogenetic Nomenclature 2009 (ISCN2009)."],"after":["Fluorescent in situ hybridization (FISH) refers to using fluorescently labeled probe to hybridize to cytogenetic cell preparations.","In addition to standard preparations FISH can also be performed on:"]}}}